  "doc_id": "55006",
  "text": "Here we propose a unified approach to the tether formation process. Building on the physics of the process, we construct a mathematical model that provides what are, to our knowledge, new insights. We establish a necessary and sufficient condition for a crossover to occur, and a formula for calculating the crossover time. We discuss conditions needed for a tether to establish a dynamic equilibrium. We derive a general mathematical formula for the tether material describing both phases of tether growth and introduce two general tether parameters, the spring constant and effective viscosity, which are valid before and after crossover. We present a modeling method which can be used to describe results of tether pulling processes, and apply the method to simulate three typical pulling processes and three pulling experiments of Shao et al. (4), Evans et al. [CITATION_1] and Heinrich et al. [CITATION_2] , and Xu and Shao [CITATION_3] .",
